    "The probability that the first response is preferred is computed as",
    "where µ denotes a sigmoid function, ϕ(e) ∈ R d is the embedding of base judge's rationale, p is the probability that the base judge prefers the first response, θ ∈ R d+1 is a learned model parameter, and c is a population bias.",
    "We estimate p using the next token probability in e (Gu et al., 2025, Section 2.3.3).",
    "The first response is preferred when π(e, p; θ) > 0.5; otherwise the second one is preferred.",
    "The population bias c plays the same role as the bias term in logistic regression."
  ],
